  <h2 id="shortcut">Setting a Keyboard Shortcut</h2>

  <p>A keyboard shortcut can be assigned to open and close the side panel.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Go to the Manage Extensions settings page (e.g. URL: <code>edge://extensions/</code>).</li>
    <li>Select the keyboard shortcuts link (e.g. URL: <code>edge://extensions/shortcuts</code>).</li>
    <li>Select the edit icon associated with the extension and focus moves to the edit box.</li>
    <li>Type the key combination for the keyboard shortcut, for example <kbd>Control</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>+<kbd>A</kbd>.</li>
    <li>When viewing a web page the shortcut can be used to open and close the side panel.</li>
  </ul>

